as derived from the medieval given name. It is more popular as a boy's name in Britain and as a girl's name in the United States."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":13,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":38,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":51,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705195,"age":105,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Jordan FitzRogus was born in 1277, in Holcombe Rogus, Devon, England, his father, Sir Henry FitzRogos, was 23 and his mother, Anne Fleming Cotton, was 17. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs Jordan ROGUS."},"et":{"1277–":"1277–Surnud","1277–Male":"1277–Surnud","1280–1360":"1280–1360","1303–1334":"1303–1334","1307–Female":"1307–Surnud","1254–1316":"1254–1316","1260–1350":"1260–1350","1275":"1275","1350":"135